			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Now recruiting:  Please submit your resume for consideration.<a name="58948"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 25 04 1:34 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>/rant on 
<br />
Some friends of mine decided that for &quot;progression&quot; they needed to join an EP flagged guild. 
<br />

<br />
I looked at the guild's website and they want you to submit an application, a completed magelo profile, and explanation of what you can do for the guild.  
<br />

<br />
I just want to know when the h*ll a fantasy roleplaying video game started requiring a cover letter, an application form, and a resume to play?  
<br />

<br />
The scary thing to me is that most people seem to consider this the norm and have no problems with this.  Does no one else consider this over the top? 
<br />

<br />
P.S.  I'm still pissed that during my friends' app phase they have to be available for all raids.  The guild in question doesn't announce raids; they go after &quot;targets of opportunity.&quot;  So for the next month or so of the trial period,  my friends aren't doing anything except XP'ing in Tactics in case a raid comes up.  
<br />

<br />
To my &quot;phat-lewt whore&quot; friends:  I hope it's worth it.  
<br />
 
<br />
/rant off.  
<br />
</span></td>
