				<td colspan="2"><span>Crewner, it's clear that you have different goals and expectations in EQ. Perhaps progression isn't a huge goal for you, but others want to really see all there is in EQ. And it's not just riding people's coattails. 
<br />

<br />
I'm in an elemental raiding organization (not really a guild, but I'll call it one), and we progressed on our own, starting with little stuff like BoT towers (in fact, we started out with the goal of farming BoT towers), and now we've passed Xegony. Sure, we take new recruits, and see people leave for the even higher-end game, but that's the nature of things. We don't ride coattails, nor do people ride ours.
<br />

<br />
Your characterization of your &quot;friends&quot; as &quot;phat-lewt whores&quot; is pretty pathetic though. People join high-end guilds for all kinds of reasons. It's not like getting into one guarantees loot or anything. I've never spent a point in over a year of raiding, for example. People often want to see, and beat the toughest mobs, work together with 71 other people to win, others want to see zones that most people can't. Sure, loots are nice, but few and far between. I think you should try to understand what the high-end game is like before calling people interested in it &quot;loot-whores&quot; or anything of the sort.</span></td>
